Information Collection and Use
We collect several different types of information for various purposes to provide and improve our Service to you.
Types of Data Collected
Personal Data
While using our Service, we may ask you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information that can be used to contact or identify you (“Personal Data”). Personally identifiable information may include, but is not limited to:
Email address
Contact number
First name and last name
Address, State, Province, ZIP/Postal code, City
Cookies and Usage Data
Card PolicyPageStyles.StyledDetails for payment
We may use your Personal Data to contact you with newsletters and other information that may be of interest to you. You may opt out of receiving any, or all, of these communications from us by following the unsubscribe link.
Usage Data
We may also collect information that your browser sends whenever you visit our Service or when you access Service by or through a mobile device (“Usage Data”).
This Usage Data may include information such as your device’s Internet Protocol address (e.g. IP address), device type, device version, the pages of our Service that you visit, the time and date of your visit, the time spent on those pages, unique device identifiers and other diagnostic data.
When you access Service with a mobile device, this Usage Data may include information such as the type of mobile device you use, your mobile device unique ID, the IP address of your mobile device, your mobile operating system, the type of mobile Internet browser you use, unique device identifiers and other diagnostic data.
Chat Functionality:
Our application includes an instant chat feature that allows you to communicate in real-time with other users. We may collect and store data related to your interactions through this chat functionality, including message content, timestamps.
Video Editor Functionality:
Our application includes a video editor feature that allows you to create and edit videos. To utilize this functionality, you may need to grant access to your device's camera and gallery. This access enables you to upload videos directly from your camera or gallery for editing within the app.
Go Live Functionality:
Our application offers a "Go Live" feature that allows you to stream live video content directly from the app. To use this functionality, you may need to grant access to your device's camera and microphone. This access enables you to broadcast live video and audio to other users in real-time.
Tracking Technologies on Mobile Applications
We use various tracking technologies to monitor activity on our Service and to retain certain information within our mobile applications. These technologies include local storage and similar methods.
Local storage in mobile applications consists of files containing a small amount of data, which may include an anonymous unique identifier. This data is stored locally on your mobile device. Additional tracking technologies such as beacons, tags, and scripts are also employed to collect and monitor information, as well as to enhance and analyze our Service.
You can configure your mobile device settings to refuse all tracking or to notify you when tracking is being used. However, if you choose to disable tracking, you may not be able to use some portions of our Service.
Here are some examples of the types of tracking technologies we use in our mobile applications:
Session Storage:
Used to operate our Service during a session.
Preference Storage:
Used to remember your preferences and various settings.
Security Storage:
Used for security purposes.
Advertising Identifiers:
Used to deliver advertisements that may be relevant to you and your interests.
Location Data:
We use your location data to deliver products and provide location-based services. This data helps us improve our service delivery and ensure accurate and timely delivery of products to your location.
Notification Permission:
We use notification permissions to send you important updates, alerts, and promotional messages. This allows us to keep you informed about the status of your orders, new features, and special offers.
Gallery Access Permission:
We request access to your device's gallery to allow you to upload videos to our application. This permission enables you to share content, customize your experience, and fully utilize features that involve video uploads.
Camera Access Permission:
We request access to your device's camera to enable you to capture photos and videos directly within our application. This access is essential for features such as video uploads, live streaming, and updating profiles.
