Termination
Grounds for Termination
Trend reserves the right to terminate or suspend your account at our sole discretion, without prior notice, if we determine that you have breached our Terms of Service, Privacy Policy, or any other applicable policies. Grounds for termination include, but are not limited to:
Violating any applicable laws or regulations.
Engaging in fraudulent, abusive, or harmful activities.
Posting content that is defamatory, obscene, discriminatory, or infringes on the rights of others.
Engaging in spamming, harassment, or other disruptive behaviors.
Posting content that is inflammatory or amounts to hate-speech.
Targeting a particular community or race or gender.
Inactivity:
Accounts that have been inactive for an extended period of time may be subject to termination.
Effect of Termination
If your account is terminated, you will lose access to the app and all its features, including but not limited to:
Loss of access to your account and user data, including your posted videos, comments, product listings, and purchase history.
Inability to interact with other users, post new content, or engage in buying or selling activities.
Upon termination, we reserve the right to delete your user data and content. However, some information may be retained for legal or operational reasons as outlined in our Privacy Policy.
If you believe your account has been terminated in error, you may contact our support team for further assistance. We will review your case and determine if any actions can be taken to reinstate your account.
By using our app, you acknowledge and agree to these termination policies and the consequences of violating them.
